g\" data-width=\"1897\" data-height=\"1068\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf there’s one thing that \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://jalopnik.com/these-are-the-things-still-keeping-you-from-buying-an-e-1851620424\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://jalopnik.com/these-are-the-things-still-keeping-you-from-buying-an-e-1851620424\"\u003ethe electric car revolution has brought to the world\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, it’s the democratization of performance. Regular family sedans are now capable of delivering the kinds of speeds previously only reached by seven-figure hypercars. You can daily drive \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://jalopnik.com/electric-sports-cars-really-dont-need-1-000-horsepower-1847632582\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://jalopnik.com/electric-sports-cars-really-dont-need-1-000-horsepower-1847632582\"\u003esomething with 1,000 horsepower\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e and a sub-two-second 0-60 time that\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://jalopnik.com/2025-porsche-taycan-gts-is-the-gold-standard-of-perform-1851703513\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://jalopnik.com/2025-porsche-taycan-gts-is-the-gold-standard-of-perform-1851703513\"\u003e doesn’t cost a million dollars or require a firesuit\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e. That’s pretty cool, isn’t it? There are even a few somewhat affordable models that make driving an EV kind of fun. I’m thinking Ford Mustang Mach-E Rally or Hyundai Ioniq 5 N here.  - Bradley Brownell \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;